angular-frontend/
├── src/
│   ├── app/                           # Contains Angular app-specific code
│   │   ├── form/                      # Form-specific component code
│   │   │   ├── form.component.ts      # TypeScript logic for the form
│   │   │   ├── form.component.html    # HTML template for the form
│   │   │   ├── form.component.css     # CSS for the form styling
│   │   └── app.module.ts              # Main Angular module for the app
│   ├── index.html                     # Entry point for the Angular app
├── angular.json                       # Angular CLI configuration file
├── package.json                       # Node.js dependencies and project metadata
├── tsconfig.json                      # TypeScript configuration file
├── Dockerfile                         # Dockerfile for building and running the frontend


src/app/:
Contains your application's main logic.
Subdirectory form/ holds files for the form-related component (HTML, CSS, TypeScript).

src/index.html:
Acts as the entry point for the Angular app.

angular.json:
Configures the Angular CLI, specifying the build process, assets, and more.

package.json:
Lists all Node.js dependencies required for the app (e.g., Angular core, CLI, etc.).

tsconfig.json:
Configures TypeScript (e.g., compiler options, module resolution).

Dockerfile:
Contains instructions to build and containerize the Angular app.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
spring-backend/
├── src/
│   ├── main/
│   │   ├── java/com/example/backend/
│   │   │   └── Controller.java
│   │   └── resources/
│   │       └── application.properties
├── pom.xml
├── Dockerfile
Java Files:
Found in src/main/java/com/example/backend/.
The folder com/example/backend reflects the Java package com.example.backend.
Configuration Files:
Found in src/main/resources/.
Build and Docker Configuration:
Found at the root level of the project: pom.xml and Dockerfile.
